body:
You can get only the first unique occurance of UID's with a hash.
Untested code below. I'm assuming the file has a UID followed by a
home path seperated by whitespace.

my %data;
while(<$fileHandle>) {
  my($UID, $home) = split /\s/;
  $data[$UID] = $home if ( ! defined $data[$UID] );
}

